      "full_name": "The Kaluga Engine Company (PJSC KADVI)",
      "is_primary": true
    }
  ],
  "remarks": "The Kaluga Engine Company (PJSC KADVI) is a Russian military industry company delivering tank engines to the other military plants producing T-80 tanks. T-80 tanks have been used during the invasion of Ukraine. Russia has recently decided to commence the serial production of T-80 tanks equipped with GTD-1250 gas turbine engines. Modernised T-80 tanks with GTD-1250 gas turbine engines are being delivered to the frontline in Ukraine.",
  "@context": "https://www.ammitto.org/ontology/context.jsonld"
}